.nh
.TH aim 1

.SH NAME
.PP
aim - Manage AppImages as desktop apps on Linux


.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
aim


.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
aim manages AppImages on Linux. It installs, integrates, updates, and removes AppImages while keeping desktop integration and a local managed-app database in sync.


.SH VERSION
.PP
dev


.SH AUTHOR
.PP
Sebastian Lobbe slobbe@lobbe.cc
\[la]mailto:slobbe@lobbe.cc\[ra]


.SH COPYRIGHT
.PP
Copyright (c) 2025 Sebastian Lobbe


.SH USAGE
.PP
.RS

.nf
aim [GLOBAL OPTIONS] [command [COMMAND OPTIONS]] [ARGUMENTS...]

.fi
.RE


.SH COMMANDS
.SH add
.PP
Add a remote source, managed app, or local AppImage

.PP
\fB--asset string\fP: asset filename pattern override for github:/gitlab: add sources

.PP
\fB--sha256 string\fP: expected SHA-256 for direct https:// add sources

.SH integrate
.PP
Integrate a local AppImage or reintegrate an existing ID

.SH remove, rm
.PP
Remove or unlink a managed AppImage

.PP
\fB--unlink\fP: remove only desktop integration; keep managed AppImage files

.SH list, ls
.PP
List managed AppImages

.PP
\fB--all, -a\fP: list all AppImages (default)

.PP
\fB--integrated, -i\fP: list integrated AppImages only

.PP
\fB--unlinked, -u\fP: list unlinked AppImages only

.SH show
.PP
Show installability details for a package ref

.SH info
.PP
Show package, managed app, or AppImage details

.SH inspect
.PP
Inspect a managed app or local AppImage

.SH install, i
.PP
Install from a remote source

.PP
\fB--asset string\fP: asset filename pattern override for github:/gitlab: install sources

.PP
\fB--sha256 string\fP: expected SHA-256 for direct https:// install sources

.SH update, u
.PP
Check or apply updates, or set an update source

.PP
.RS

.nf
aim update [<id>] [--yes|-y] [--check-only|-c]
   aim update set <id> (--github owner/repo [--asset "*.AppImage"] | --gitlab namespace/project [--asset "*.AppImage"] | --zsync-url <https-url> | --embedded)
   aim update unset <id>

.fi
.RE

.PP
\fB--yes, -y\fP: apply updates without prompting

.PP
\fB--check-only, -c\fP: check only; do not apply updates

.PP
\fB--github string\fP: GitHub repo in the form owner/repo (for 'update set')

.PP
\fB--asset string\fP: asset filename pattern; defaults to "*.AppImage" for GitHub/GitLab (for 'update set')

.PP
\fB--gitlab string\fP: GitLab project path namespace/project (for 'update set')

.PP
\fB--zsync-url string\fP: direct zsync metadata URL (https, for 'update set')

.PP
\fB--embedded\fP: use the update source embedded in the current AppImage (for 'update set')

.SH upgrade
.PP
Upgrade aim to the latest stable release
